Diagnostic and treatment principles, methods and tactics of urological diseases. The course is a part of the subject "Surgery" (12 CP)Objectives/eesmärkid:  To teach the epidemiology, etio-pathogenesis, urodiagnostics, classification of diseases, clinical picture, treatment principles (open surgery and endoscopic surgery), prognosis and prophylaxis of urological and uro-oncological diseases, including more common uroogical pathologies.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student 1) is able to diagnose more common urological pathologies; 2) has an understanding of the performing of diagnostic procedures ad their indications; 3) has general comprehension of contemporary treatment principles of urological diseases.
